data.title: Mobix Labs granted 180-day extension by Nasdaq to regain compliance with minimum bid price requirement.
data.description: In Irvine, California on October 30, 2025, Mobix Labs, Inc. (Nasdaq: MOBX) revealed it secured a 180-day extension from the Nasdaq Stock Market to meet the minimum bid price requirement per Nasdaq Listing Rule 5550(a)(2). The company specializes in advanced wireless and wired connectivity, RF, switching, and filtering technologies for upcoming communication systems. This extension provides additional time for Mobix Labs to fulfill the compliance standards.

data.title: City Ventures' Towns on First in Downtown Upland almost sold out with final homes release this weekend, reflecting high demand.
data.description: In Upland, California, Towns on First, a townhome-style community by City Ventures, is experiencing rapid home sales. As California's top builder of eco-friendly homes with solar panels included, City Ventures revealed that the last phase of homes at Towns on First will be available this Saturday, November 1. The high demand from buyers looking to reside in the walkable Downtown Upland area is evident in the quick sales. Reflecting the shift in buyer preferences, modern homebuyers seek more than just a house, seeking eco-conscious and sustainable features.

data.title: Polygraf AI secures $9.5M funding led by Allegis Capital for scaling secure AI solutions. Expanding products and markets.
data.description: An Austin-based company, Polygraf AI, recently concluded a seed funding round amounting to $9.5 million. Allegis Capital led the investment, with participation from Alumni Ventures, DataPower VC, and Domino Ventures alongside existing investors. The primary objective behind this funding is to expedite their objective of enhancing transparency and reliability in enterprise AI. The fresh capital injection will be utilized for expanding products, furthering research and development activities, and bolstering market penetration particularly targeting the enterprise, defense, and intelligence segments. The financial backing received by Polygraf AI marks a significant development in their journey.

data.title: Mid-Southern Bancorp, Inc. sets dissolution payment range at $17.45-$17.75 per share; record date is Nov 10, distribution by Nov 14.
data.description: In Salem, Indiana, a financial announcement was made by Mid-Southern Bancorp, Inc. on Oct. 28, 2025. The company (OTC Pink: MSVB), formerly the parent of Mid-Southern Savings Bank, FSB, revealed that shareholders are anticipated to receive approximately $17.45 to $17.75 in cash per share of common stock held, calculated based on the Company's financial status as of September 30, 2025. This per share consideration is set to be distributed to shareholders listed on record by November 10, 2025. Following this date, the Company's common stock will be delisted from the OTC Pink Marketplace, ceasing stock trading activity. The Company expects the dissolution distribution to be completed around November 14, 2025; the exact delisting date will not be confirmed by the Company, and no notification will be provided upon implementation.

data.title: MediciNova's study shows tipelukast has influence on cholesterol metabolism in patients, published in Journal of Atherosclerosis and Thrombosis.
data.description: A recent study featured in the Journal of Atherosclerosis and Thrombosis has shown that tipelukast (MN-001) and its metabolite MN-002 impact cholesterol metabolism in patients. This research sheds light on the effects of these compounds on cholesterol regulation. The findings of this study provide valuable insights into the potential role of tipelukast in managing cholesterol levels. This study is significant as it addresses the influence of tipelukast on cholesterol metabolism, highlighting its potential as a therapeutic option. This study adds to the growing body of evidence supporting the use of tipelukast in patients with dyslipidemia.

data.title: Micron adjusts investor event time from 7:20 a.m. to 6:00 a.m. Mountain Time.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, Micron Technology, Inc. (Nasdaq: MU) announced a change in the time of their upcoming conference. Originally scheduled for 7:20 a.m. Mountain Time, the conference will now take place at 6:00 a.m. Mountain Time.

data.title: The Lemon Pros introduced a free Car Recall Check Tool to help drivers spot safety defects early.
data.description: A prominent California lemon law and consumer rights firm known as The Lemon Pros, based in Beverly Hills, recently introduced a new Car Recall Check Tool. This innovative tool is available for free and aids drivers in recognizing safety flaws in their vehicles before they escalate into expensive or hazardous issues. The interactive tool offers a way for drivers to check for recalls on their vehicles, helping them stay informed about potential safety hazards. This initiative aims to empower drivers with crucial information about their vehicles and prevent potential dangers on the road. The tool allows individuals to proactively address any identified safety defects, promoting safer driving practices. The Car Recall Check Tool is a significant advancement by The Lemon Pros in their commitment to protecting consumers' rights and ensuring road safety.

data.title: Top official sold his Fiserv stock before it crashed, potentially saving millions. Bisignano worked at SSA and IRS.
data.description: Frank Bisignano, an individual holding prominent positions at the Social Security Administration and the I.R.S., recently divested his ownership in Fiserv prior to the company's stock plummeting this week.

data.title: Cephia raises $4M seed funding, aims to innovate multimodal sensing with metasurface technology in Silicon Valley.
data.description: A startup, Cephia, founded by accomplished innovators in computational imaging from Princeton University, is operating in San Francisco. Established on Oct. 30, 2025, the company specializes in creating products through AI computational imaging technologies. Cephia utilizes silicon sensors crafted from cutting-edge metamaterials for its operations.

data.title: Amazon reported Q3 FY2025 earnings: $180.2B revenue, $17.4B operating income. AWS growing 20.2% YoY, backlog at $200B. Stores innovating for customers with expanded selection, prices, and faster delivery. Ads revenue $17.6B, 22% growth YoY.
data.description: Amazon.com, Inc. released its third-quarter 2025 earnings report showing $180.2 billion in revenue, a 12% increase year over year (excluding foreign exchange impact). The operating income was $17.4 billion, which could have been over $21 billion if not for two special expenses. Amazon Web Services (AWS) saw significant growth, with a 20.2% year-over-year increase, reaching a backlog of $200 billion by the end of the quarter. AWS is gaining momentum in core and AI workloads due to its functionality and performance. The company continues to innovate in AI, launching new features like Amazon Bedrock and Amazon Curo. The Stores division also showed innovation and growth, offering more selection, low prices, and convenience, including fast delivery options. Amazon's advertising business generated $17.6 billion in revenue, growing 22% year over year, with partnerships with companies like Netflix, Spotify, and Sirius XM. The company is investing heavily in capacity expansion to meet growing customer demand.

data.title: Black Diamond increases dividend after reporting Q3 2025 results. Provider of space rental and workforce solutions.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, in Calgary, Alberta, Black Diamond Group Limited disclosed its operational and financial outcomes for the three and nine months concluding on September 30, 2025. The company, a key supplier of space rental and workforce lodging options, revealed these results in comparison to the data from the equivalent periods ending on September 30, 2024. The financials provided are denominated in Canadian dollars. Black Diamond's stock is listed on the Toronto Stock Exchange as BDI and on the OTCQX as BDIMF.

data.title: ANSI releases Oct. 2025 Gaps Progress Report for EV standards to boost safe adoption nationwide.
data.description: In a move to promote the safe and extensive use of electric vehicles (EVs) and their infrastructure throughout the country, the American National Standards Institute (ANSI) unveiled the October 2025 Gaps Progress Report in New York on October 30th, 2025. The report provides crucial updates on the gaps currently present in the EV industry.

data.title: Atlassian Corp's Q1 revenue exceeds estimates at $1.43B, with adjusted earnings at $1.04/share. Cloud revenue grew by 26%.
data.description: Atlassian Corp (NASDAQ: TEAM) released their first quarter fiscal 2026 financial results, exceeding expectations and presenting strong numbers. The company reported $1.43 billion in revenue for Q1, surpassing analyst projections of $1.40 billion. Their adjusted earnings for the quarter were $1.04 per share, higher than the anticipated 84 cents per share. Atlassian saw a 21% year-over-year increase in total revenue, with Cloud revenue specifically growing by 26%. In terms of cash flow, they generated $129 million. This positive performance has positioned Atlassian among the top performers for the day. For more detailed insights, analysts recommend checking out further analysis on the matter.

data.title: Rosewood Hong Kong tops list of world's best hotels 2025 in London ceremony with 20 Asian hotels in top 50.
data.description: The prestigious announcement of the world's best hotels for 2025 included properties from 22 different destinations spanning six continents. The live ceremony in London revealed Rosewood Hong Kong as the top-ranked hotel globally. The list also highlighted 20 hotels from Asia, showcasing the region's strong presence. Special awards were also presented during the event, recognizing exceptional hospitality achievements in the industry.

data.title: Dr. Antoanella Calame named in San Diego's 2025 "Top Doctors" list for Dermatopathology.
data.description: In San Diego on October 30, 2025, Compass Dermatopathology is pleased to reveal that its leader, Antoanella Calame, MD, a certified dermatologist and dermatopathologist, has been recognized as one of the "Top Doctors" in Dermatopathology for the year 2025.

data.title: Timberland Bancorp's 2025 fiscal year net income increased to $29.16 million EPS rose to $3.67. A new branch in University Place announced.
data.description: Timberland Bancorp, Inc. reported strong financial results with net income increasing 20% to $29.16 million for the fiscal year ended September 30, 2025. Earnings per diluted common share ("EPS") increased by 22% to $3.67. Quarterly EPS increased by 19% to $1.07. Quarterly net interest margin increased to 3.82%, Return on Average Assets to 1.68%, and Return on Average Equity to 12.97%. The company announced an 8% increase in the quarterly cash dividend to $0.28 per share and plans to open a branch in University Place. Total assets reached $2.0 billion with a 3% increase, while total deposits increased by 3% and shareholders' equity increased by 2%. Non-performing assets to total assets ratio was 0.23%. Timberland originated $100.09 million in loans during the quarter. Total deposits increased by $47.16 million to $1.72 billion. Total shareholders' equity increased by 2% to $262.61 million. The company remains well capitalized with a total risk-based capital ratio of 20.67% and a Tier 1 leverage capital ratio of 12.59%.
